dt-option.default:
        The default value for the `-init searchPanes.hide` paramater is `false`. When this default value is in place the button which allows the panes to be collapsed will be shown.


        As standard, SearchPanes will display the button which allow the panes to be collapsible. When `-init searchPanes.hide` is set to `false`, the button will not be attached to the document.

		The `-init searchPanes.hide` functionality is useful when using the panes in a busy or confined space as it allows them to be hidden when they are not in use.





$(document).ready(function() {
    $('#example').DataTable( {
        searchPanes:{
            hide: false
        }
    });
});
